{"books":{"7":{"id":"3344","title":"Melting of Molly","description":"<p>Meet Molly: a quirky, spirited twenty-five-year old, widowed for 6 years, living in picturesque Hillsboro with her aunt amidst gossipy neighbors, on a strict diet, and in serious boy trouble. There's Arthur, her childhood sweetheart; then, there's the enigmatic, charming Judge Wade; and of course, there's her cousin Tom; and then, her infuriating neighbor, John Moore... But who will melt her heart?<br><br>It is Arthur's return, and his seemingly simple request of wanting to see her in the same blue dress she wore when he left, that throws everything into turmoil...<br><br>Sometimes, one can only find some solace in one's garden.<br><br>Narrated in a refreshingly modern and playful style by none other than Molly herself, this book is the British magazine version; there\u2019s a significantly different American novel version.(Summary by Elli, Julie VW and Stav Nisser)<\/p>","url_text_source":"http:\/\/www.gutenberg.org\/ebooks\/15818","language":"English","copyright_year":"1912","num_sections":"8","url_rss":"http:\/\/librivox.org\/rss\/3344","url_zip_file":"http:\/\/www.archive.org\/download\/melting_of_molly_0908_librivox\/melting_of_molly_0908_librivox_64kb_mp3.zip","url_project":"","url_librivox":"http:\/\/librivox.org\/the-melting-of-molly-by-maria-thompson-daviess\/","url_other":null,"totaltime":"2:29:33","totaltimesecs":8973,"authors":[{"id":"5266","first_name":" Maria Thompson","last_name":"Daviess","dob":"1872","dod":"1924"}],"url_iarchive":"http:\/\/www.archive.org\/details\/melting_of_molly_0908_librivox","sections":[{"id":"184445","section_number":"1","title":" Leaf I. The Bachelor's-Buttons.","listen_url":"","language":"English","playtime":"941","file_name":null,"readers":[{"reader_id":"3885","display_name":"Elli"}]},{"id":"184446","section_number":"2","title":" Leaf II. A Love-Letter, Loaded. ","listen_url":"","language":"English","playtime":"1003","file_name":null,"readers":[{"reader